### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Multi-Agent: Article Sub-Agent Test Suite
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### Pre-requisites:
###   1. Run seed_vehicles.http first (seeds BMW M3, Porsche 911, etc.)
###   2. Run cms_article_test.http sections 1-2 (ingests M3 review + comparison article)
###   3. Spring Boot app running on localhost:8080
###   4. Ollama running with llama3.1 + nomic-embed-text
###
### Test order:
###   Phase 1: Verify data is seeded (read-only checks)
###   Phase 2: Article agent via multi-agent supervisor
###   Phase 3: Article → Vehicle shared tool (the key inter-agent test)
###   Phase 4: Article + Communication (multi-delegation)
###   Phase 5: Edge cases
###
### Endpoint: POST /agent/multi (MultiAgentController)
### Same request/response shape as POST /agent (single-agent)
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════


### ── Phase 1: Verify seed data exists ─────────────────────────────────

### 1.1 Check vehicle chunks exist (BMW M3)
### Expected: count > 0
### 1.1 Check vehicle chunks exist (BMW M3)
### Expected: answer mentioning 503hp, S58 engine
POST http://localhost:8080/vehicles/bmw-m3-2025-competition/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is the horsepower?",
  "topK": 3
}

###

### 1.2 Check article chunks exist (M3 review)
### Expected: answer about M3 performance
POST http://localhost:8080/articles/motortrend-bmw-m3-2025-review/ask
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "What is the M3's horsepower?",
  "topK": 3,
  "mode": "HYBRID"
}

###


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Phase 2: Article agent basic flows via supervisor
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2.1 Single-article ask — routes to article agent
### Supervisor should plan: [{agent: "article", args: {articleId: "..."}}]
### Expected: LLM-synthesized answer about M3 track performance
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What did MotorTrend say about the BMW M3's performance on track? Article ID is motortrend-bmw-m3-2025-review",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.global.set("sessionId", response.body.sessionId);
    client.log("Session: " + response.body.sessionId);
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
%}

###

### 2.2 Cross-article search — routes to article agent
### Supervisor should plan: [{agent: "article"}]
### Expected: mentions M3 as top-rated, comparison article also surfaces
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Which sports sedan was rated best by MotorTrend?",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.global.set("sessionId", response.body.sessionId);
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
%}

###

### 2.3 Vehicle-scoped article search — find all articles about BMW M3
### Supervisor should plan: [{agent: "article", args: {vehicleQuery: "BMW M3"}}]
### Expected: both M3 review and comparison article
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Find all articles and reviews about the BMW M3 2025",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
%}

###

### 2.4 Rating-based search — articles rated over 9
### Expected: both articles (rated 9.2), LLM synthesizes from ratings chunks
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Show me articles rated over 9 out of 10",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
%}

###


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Phase 3: Article → Vehicle shared tool (INTER-AGENT COMMUNICATION)
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### This is the key test. The article agent should:
###   Phase 1: Search articles → finds M3 review + comparison
###   Phase 2: Extract vehicleId "bmw-m3-2025-competition" from article ID
###            Call FetchVehicleSpecsTool (shared with VehicleSubAgent)
###            Get spec chunks from the vehicle domain's pgvector data
###   Phase 3: Merge article + spec chunks → LLM synthesizes unified answer
###
### The supervisor sends ONE delegation to article agent. The vehicle spec
### fetch happens internally — supervisor doesn't know about it.
###
### Look for in the response:
###   - answer mentions both article ratings AND vehicle specs (hp, engine)
###   - citations include both article chunk IDs (motortrend-...:N)
###     and vehicle spec chunk IDs (bmw-m3-2025-competition:N)

### 3.1 Top-ranked articles with vehicle specs
### THE MAIN TEST — triggers executeVehicleEnrichedSearch
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Show me top ranked vehicle articles with specs for sports sedans",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.global.set("sessionId", response.body.sessionId);
    client.log("=== INTER-AGENT TEST ===");
    client.log("Answer: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 300));
    client.log("Citations: " + JSON.stringify(response.body.citations));
    // Check for both article and vehicle citations
    var hasArticleCitation = response.body.citations?.some(c => c.startsWith("motortrend-"));
    var hasVehicleCitation = response.body.citations?.some(c => c.startsWith("bmw-m3-"));
    client.log("Has article citations: " + hasArticleCitation);
    client.log("Has vehicle citations: " + hasVehicleCitation);
%}

###

### 3.2 Inspect the session to see the article agent's internal steps
GET http://localhost:8080/agent/{{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 3.3 Best rated with vehicle specifications — alternate phrasing
### Should also trigger vehicle-enriched search
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What are the best rated cars with their specifications and performance data?",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 300));
%}

###

### 3.4 Highest rated with vehicle details — another trigger phrase
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Show me the highest rated sports sedans with vehicle specs and images",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
%}

###

### 3.5 Explicit vehicleIds in prompt — supervisor might pass these in args
### Tests that article agent uses explicit IDs instead of extracting from articleId
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Show me top ranked articles with specs for bmw-m3-2025-competition and cadillac-ct4v-2025-blackwing",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Citations: " + JSON.stringify(response.body.citations));
%}

###


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Phase 4: Article + Communication (multi-delegation flow)
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### Supervisor should plan TWO delegations:
###   1. {agent: "article", task: "find top rated articles with specs"}
###   2. {agent: "communication", task: "email the result"}
###
### Article agent runs first → produces content.
### Communication agent runs second → uses article content as email body.

### 4.1 Article search + email
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Find the top rated sports sedan articles with vehicle specs and email the results to hr@company.com",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.global.set("sessionId", response.body.sessionId);
    client.log("Status: " + response.body.emailStatus);
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
%}

###

### 4.2 Inspect session — should show delegate_article + delegate_communication steps
GET http://localhost:8080/agent/{{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4.3 Article search + SMS
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is the best rated sports sedan? Text the answer to +15551234567",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Status: " + response.body.emailStatus);
%}

###


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Phase 5: Edge cases and routing verification
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 5.1 Pure vehicle question — should route to vehicle agent, NOT article
### Verify supervisor picks "vehicle" not "article"
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What are the specs of the BMW M3 Competition?",
  "topK": 3
}

> {%
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
%}

###

### 5.2 Pure research question — should route to research agent
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "docId": "spring-boot-qa",
  "prompt": "What is Spring Boot auto-configuration?",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
%}

###

### 5.3 Ambiguous article vs vehicle — "tell me about the M3"
### Could go either way. Interesting to see how supervisor routes it.
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Tell me everything about the 2025 BMW M3 Competition — reviews, ratings, specs, performance",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.global.set("sessionId", response.body.sessionId);
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 300));
%}

###

### 5.4 Inspect the ambiguous routing session
### Look at history → which agent(s) did the supervisor choose?
GET http://localhost:8080/agent/{{sessionId}}
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 5.5 No matching articles — should fail gracefully
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Show me top ranked articles about electric boats with specs",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Answer: " + response.body.answer);
    client.log("Status: " + response.body.emailStatus);
%}

###

### 5.6 Vehicle not ingested — article agent finds articles but spec fetch returns empty
### Should still succeed with article-only content (graceful degradation)
### Use a vehicle that has articles but no vehicle domain data
POST http://localhost:8080/agent/multi
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Show me top ranked articles with specs for the Mercedes AMG C63",
  "topK": 5
}

> {%
    client.log("Answer preview: " + response.body.answer?.substring(0, 200));
    // Citations should include article chunks but NOT vehicle spec chunks
    // (because mercedes-amg-c63-2025 is not in the vehicle domain)
    client.log("Citations: " + JSON.stringify(response.body.citations));
%}

###


### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### Quick reference: what to check in each phase
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
###
### Phase 2 (basic article):
###   ✓ Supervisor routes to "article" agent (check session history)
###   ✓ LLM-synthesized answer (not template text)
###   ✓ Citations reference article chunk IDs
###
### Phase 3 (inter-agent — THE KEY TESTS):
###   ✓ Answer contains BOTH article content (ratings, verdict)
###     AND vehicle specs (horsepower, engine, 0-60)
###   ✓ Citations include BOTH motortrend-*:N AND bmw-m3-*:N chunk IDs
###   ✓ Session history shows only ONE delegation (article), not two
###   ✓ Graceful degradation when vehicle specs unavailable (test 5.6)
###
### Phase 4 (article + communication):
###   ✓ Two delegations in session history: article → communication
###   ✓ emailStatus is "DRAFTED" or "SENT"
###   ✓ Article content was passed as email body
###
### Phase 5 (routing):
###   ✓ Pure vehicle → routes to vehicle agent (not article)
###   ✓ Pure research → routes to research agent
###   ✓ No results → fails gracefully, no 500 error
